Where will you be watching the 50th Super Bowl












If you cant make it to California this year to watch the Super Bowl fear not you can watch all the action in Cardiff Heres everything you need to know about one of the biggest sporting events in the US calendar and where you can watch it in the Welsh capital What is the Super Bowl The Super Bowl is the annual championship game of the National Football League NFL the highest level of professional football in the US Where and when is it In 2016 it will be the 50th edition of the Super Bowl and it will be held at the Levis Stadium in Santa Clara California home of the San Francisco 49ers on February 7 





Poll loading hellip




 Which teams are playing The 50th Super Bowl is between the Carolina Panthers and the Denver Broncos When is it on in the UK 



 In the UK Panthers v Broncos kicks off at 1130pm on Sunday February 7 Where can I see it in Cardiff WALKABOUT Head to Walkabout the Australian chain bar popular for its bigscreen sports coverage Walkabout 6574 St Mary St Cardiff CF10 1FA What can I expect to see A great viewing experience with big screens and full live HD commentary in a party atmosphere Watch the buildup from around 10pm with Walkabouts real time statistics team profiles and live social media feeds shown alongside highlights from the NFL on the screens The venue will be filled with all things NFL including the food drinks and decor Youll also get to see the halftime entertainment which this year features British band Coldplay Can I order food 



 You can preorder a party package that includes a hot dog meal three chicken wings and two bottles of Budweiser for only pound12 Do I need a ticket No but to guarantee a good view of the screen and table service its best to book on wwwwalkaboutbarscoukSuperBowl Heres where else in Cardiff you can see the Super Bowl and if you know of somewhere not mentioned pop it in the comments box below   SHOOTERS SPORTS BAR 


Shooters Sports Bar



 Watch the game on a HD screen thats so big youll think youre on the pitch The Cardiff venue is taking bookings for the event for groups of all sizes Just give them a call on 08455 333 000 or fill in their online booking enquiry form Shooters Stadium Plaza Wood Street Cardiff CF10 1LA 


Shooters Sports Bar



 The standard menu has burgers hot dogs pizzas ribs chicken salads and sharing platters as well as classics like chilli pie lasagne and wraps Shooters also offers a number of Americanstyle VIP packages The pound10ahead bronze package gives you a free shot hot dog or burger VIP seating in front of a big screen and dedicated waitress service Upgrade to the pound15ahead silver package which includes two bottles of Budweiser or the gold package which costs pound20 a head and includes everything youd get in both bronze and silver plus an additional Shooters Food Platter THE BUNKER 



 Make it a night to remember and book a booth for you and your friends at the Bunker Rock Lounge amp Sports Bar Youll need to buy a ticket which costs pound60 for a booth or pound3 for a standard entry ticket There are food and drink deals available too so you can eat drink and be merry while cheering on your favourite team Its open from 9pm on the night to 4am on the Monday The Bunker 6061 St Mary Street Cardiff CF10 1FE       



















